  "body": "As title, if you attempt to scale an rc similar to this one:\n\n```\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ReplicationController\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    db: rethinkdb\n  name: rethinkdb\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  replicas: 1\n  selector:\n    db: rethinkdb-admin\n    role: replicas\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        db: rethinkdb-admin\n        role: replicas\n    spec:\n      containers:\n      - image: [REDACTED]/kubectl-proxy\n        imagePullPolicy: 'Always'\n        name: kubeproxy\n        ports:\n        - containerPort: 8001\n          name: kubeport\n      - image: [REDACTED]/rethinkdb\n        imagePullPolicy: 'Always'\n        name: rethinkdb\n        ports:\n        - containerPort: 8080\n          name: admin-port\n        - containerPort: 28015\n          name: driver-port\n        - containerPort: 29015\n          name: cluster-port\n        volumeMounts:\n          - name: volume-name\n            mountPath: [REDACTED]\n      volumes:\n        - name: volume-name\n          gcePersistentDisk:\n            pdName: [REDACTED] \n            fsType: ext4\n```\n\n with the command:\n\n```\nkubectl scale rc rcName --replicas=2\n```\n\nThe cli will wait indefinitely while the kublet attempts to post a new pod over and over again.\n",
